{
  "stem": "23428.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So-- so we were in one of these, driven into one of these, and, [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] OK, given a place in-- in one of the blocks.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The blocks consisted of these wooden-- wooden beds, hundreds, one next to the other.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were just wooden-- wooden cases filled with straw, where always two guys slept in-- in one box together.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then I think we were woken up at 4:00, 4:00 in the morning or something like this, and recruited for labor, each labor battalion being led by a kapo.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Now, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] OK, if I said that I haven't seen any brutality in the camp except these two incidents, not true, just brutality by the SS.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "In fact, we never saw any SS again much.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "All the brutality in the camps was carried out by prisoners against prisoners, and of course, all the kapos, who did most of the brutality, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] most of the beatings.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A large majority, transport Jews.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A few-- one, I remember, was a political, Social Democrat German.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] You see, most of them actually were fellow Jewish prisoners, who-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] who obviously got that for themselves, this position of supervisor, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] for saving their own necks.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean it's, again, the story of the Aryanization of my father in a different-- different way.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I should preface this by saying, in general, you know, I've read a lot-- a lot of claims about the solidarity of prisoners under those conditions.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I must tell you I've never seen it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I've heard about solidarity in the block occupied by Russian officers, Red Army officers.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
